00:43:59.230 --> 00:44:01.350
For all the champions out
there to pay attention

00:44:01.350 --> 00:44:05.700
to all the little things that even
the experts can be expected to know.

00:44:10.420 --> 00:44:13.530
I often repeat the model,
nothing about us without us,

00:44:13.530 --> 00:44:17.650
don't enact accessibility without
talking to disabled people.

00:44:17.650 --> 00:44:20.860
There's a related saying
that is also very important,

00:44:20.860 --> 00:44:23.340
do it with us, not for us.

00:44:23.340 --> 00:44:26.390
If you implement accessibility
for disabled people,

00:44:26.390 --> 00:44:29.090
you're likely approaching
accessibility from a perspective

00:44:29.090 --> 00:44:31.890
of either charity
or legal compliance,

00:44:31.890 --> 00:44:33.840
and that's not the
frame of mind you want.

00:44:33.840 --> 00:44:37.170
It's also not the frame of mind
you have when your organization

00:44:37.170 --> 00:44:39.460
or your project has a
culture of accessibility.

